item.title: Power typical requirements
item.description:
Small Utility Tractors: 20–60 hp (15–45 kW)
Mid-size Row Crop Tractors: 100–200 hp (75–150 kW)
Large Articulated Tractors: 300–600+ hp (225–450+ kW)


Examples:
Monarch MK-V: ~70 hp (52 kW)
Solectrac e70N: ~70 hp (52 kW)
Battery Capacity: ~50–70 kWh
Charging Power Needs: 10–20 kW (Level 2 or 3)

[1]

On average, 450 hp combine harvesters which harvest 50 ha/day use around 700L of fuel every day.[2]



Power Range: 150–350 hp (110–260 kW)


Power: ~10–30 kW
Use Case: Orchards, vineyards, precision tasks



Power: 5–15 kW
Battery Capacity: 5–15 kWh
Use Case: Light hauling, inspection, fence work


Tractor Power Required: 200–500 hp (150–370 kW)




Full-electric large farm machines are limited due to:
High continuous power demands
Long runtime needs
Rural charging infrastructure challenges
Battery swapping and hybrid tractors are emerging trends
